    %    \caption{\textbf{Intergenic L1 are older than L1 in Genes\\}
    %    More here
    %    }
    %    \label{fig: l1intolder}
    %\end{figure}
    %
    
To determine if the association between location and millidiv was effected more by regions within genes versus intergenic, or sense versus antisense.  77 subfamilies had elements that were significantly different in age between intergenic and within gene regions (tests =114 ; Bonferroni corrected $\alpha$ = 4.4e-04). 76 of these 77 subfamilies were older in intergenic regions than within genes. This substantiates the hypothesis that L1 retrotransposons undergo selection within genes, though indicates that there are varying effects contributing to the selection of L1 in genes. 10 subfamilies had significant differences in age between AS and S orientations, 7 of which were older in the antisense orientation. 

