\subsection{Evidence of Purifying Selection on S and AS Alu}

As expected, within sense Alu, elements on chrX had significantly lower millidiv than those on autosomes, which were significantly less than those on chrY (table \ref{table:chrsig}). The same pattern was identified between antisense Alu and between intergenic Alu. This result showed that chromosomes with heightened ability for purifying selection had elements that were significantly younger, supporting that purifying selection is indeed acting on Alu RTs. In fact, the effect of rate of selection as identified by type of chromosome had a larger effect on element age than the orientation. For example, sense Alu on chrY were significantly older than antisense Alu on autosomes, further indicating that the antisense bias is only present when purifying selection is present. 

